One, don't forget that just because it's low effort doesn't mean that it's bad. All of technological advancement is about doing more with less effort.
Two, don't forget that the customer is always right in matters of taste. AI slop has the AI slop look because AI was trained on what people like, so it's the average of what's popular. It's doomed to be average but that's not a bad place to be. And people who are used to Walmart cake will like it better than the fancy cake that has some funny (probably real instead of imitation) ingredient that they're not used to in the mix. Both cakes and those who prefer either one over the other are all valid.

That's where artists should be turning toward AI as a force multiplier, instead of wasting energy yelling at coomers making throwaway pics.
